SUMMARY:District Arcade
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by IGDA DC\, District Arcade returns on October 25th 2025 1:00-5:00 PM at the Martin Luther King Library in DC. The meetup and lineup is still being worked on\, however the date and location have been confirmed. \nWhat is District Arcade\, you ask? It’s a free celebration of games and game makers from the DC and DMV area. Play locally-crafted indie games and chat with the devs in this fun\, family-friendly in person event. There will be 15-20 local developers showcasing games of different genres and levels of completion. \nEvent Information \n\nLocation: Lab – Bottom floor of the MLK Library\nAddress: 901 G St NW\, Washington DC\, 20001\nDate and Time: October 25th 2024 1:00-5:00 PM\nMeetup Page: https://www.meetup.com/igda-dc/events/310523499/\n\nIf you are interested in presenting at District Arcade please fill out this form: https://forms.gle/z3ikPZQnfwbbtrm2A \nSubmissions close September 30th. We have 25-30 slots so if you submit you will most likely get in.
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/district-arcade/
LOCATION:Martin Luther King Jr. Memorial Library\, 901 G St NW\, Washington\, DC\, 20001\, United States
END:VEVENT
